<subSubSection id="10C53684B5F4FF31FF23F5DB275FFBFC" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="5860650FB5F4FF31FF23F5DB25F0FC58" blockId="231.[151,1436,971,1272]" box="[151,242,971,996]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<heading id="0328D263B5F4FF31FF23F5DB25F0FC58" bold="true" box="[151,242,971,996]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FF23F5DB25F0FC58" authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1901" box="[151,242,971,996]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FF23F5DB25F0FC58" bold="true" box="[151,242,971,996]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5860650FB5F4FF31FF23F5FB275FFBFC" blockId="231.[151,1436,971,1272]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FF23F5FB24A4FBBE" authority="Hagen, 1861" authorityName="Hagen" authorityYear="1861" box="[151,422,1001,1026]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alacer">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FF23F5FB241FFBBE" box="[151,285,1002,1026]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestes alacer</emphasis>
Hagen, 1861
</taxonomicName>
. Reported by Campos (1922) from “Posorja” and 
<collectingRegion id="9A1BABEDB5F4FF31FC2CF5F926D9FBBE" box="[920,987,1001,1026]" country="Ecuador" name="El Oro" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">El Oro</collectingRegion>
(Campos 1927). This Central American species surely does not occur in 
<collectingCountry id="20C8259FB5F4FF31FE5FF2182743FB9D" box="[491,577,1032,1057]" name="Ecuador" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. These references are probably either 
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FC74F2192132FB9C" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[960,1072,1033,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuatus">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FC74F2192132FB9C" box="[960,1072,1033,1056]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">L. tenuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FBE5F21921C8FB9D" box="[1105,1226,1033,1057]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FBE5F21921C7FB9D" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1946" box="[1105,1221,1033,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Argia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">L. forficula</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the only two species verified for the west slope of the Andes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="10C53684B5F4FF31FF23F257266DFB4B" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="description">
<paragraph id="5860650FB5F4FF31FF23F25724AAFB20" blockId="231.[151,1436,971,1272]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FF23F25724D5FBE2" authority="Calvert, 1907" authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1907" box="[151,471,1093,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henshawi">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FF23F257243DFBE2" box="[151,319,1094,1118]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestes henshawi</emphasis>
Calvert, 1907
</taxonomicName>
. Publ. Recs. ECU: Soukop (1954), Paulson (1983), Tsuda (1986); 
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FB3AF25521ACFBE2" bold="true" box="[1166,1198,1093,1118]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">PA</emphasis>
: Kennedy (1942b— 
<specimenCount id="4ED9AE86B5F4FF31FA38F255209BFBE2" box="[1420,1433,1093,1118]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, described). These are all 
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FE79F275260CFBC1" authority="Navas, 1934" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[461,782,1125,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apollinaris">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FE79F2752786FBC1" box="[461,644,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestes apollinaris</emphasis>
Navás, 1934
</taxonomicName>
according to Donnelly (1996) since 
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FB3AF2752034FBC1" authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1907" box="[1166,1334,1125,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henshawi">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FB3AF2752034FBC1" box="[1166,1334,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestes henshawi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="20C8259FB5F4FF31FE86F29324A6FB20" box="[306,420,1155,1180]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5860650FB5F4FF31FF23F2B327BFFB65" blockId="231.[151,1436,971,1272]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FF23F2B324B0FB06" authority="Selys, 1862" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,434,1185,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FF23F2B3242DFB06" box="[151,303,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestes minutus</emphasis>
Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
. Reported by Campos (1922) from “Posorja”. Unlikely since it is an Atlantic coast species listed from BRA, COL, GUF VEN, TTO: (H08), (P11).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5860650FB5F4FF31FF23F2F0266DFB4B" blockId="231.[151,1436,971,1272]" box="[151,879,1247,1272]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FF23F2F024ABFB44" authority="Selys, 1862" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,425,1247,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FF23F2F0242BFB4B" box="[151,297,1248,1271]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestes striatus</emphasis>
Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
. Synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="9FDF1E8CB5F4FF31FD81F2F0266EFB4B" authority="Rambur, 1842" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[565,876,1247,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">
<emphasis id="6AABB91DB5F4FF31FD81F2F027D0FB4B" box="[565,722,1247,1271]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Lestes forficula</emphasis>
Rambur, 1842
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
